title: Otways Bioscan – Lepidoptera
description:
This lepidoptera survey is conducted by Museums Victoria and Parks Victoria in conjunction with Moths of Victoria team members.
**Observations added to this group are restricted to those made during the survey events.

Components of the Bioscan project:
•	Make comparisons between recently burnt areas with unburnt areas
•	Prepare a booklet

NOTE: Your information is valuable to the creation of a comprehensive list of species occurring in the Otways. Please join the NatureShare group    'Otway Ranges – Moths'

items.title: Udea hyalistis
items.content_text: Observed this species at this location in late October as well.

items.title: Unplaced plagiocausta
items.content_text: This is a provisional accepted name. Also known as Chrysolarentia plagiocausta

items.title: Chrysolarentia severata
items.content_text: This is a provisional accepted name. Also known as Chrysolarentia severata

items.title: Unplaced biplaga
items.content_text: Provisional accepted name. Also known as (Azelina) biplaga

items.title: Bactra spp.
items.content_text: Thanks to Cathy Powers and Peter Marriot for follow-up on ID

items.title: Epitymbia scotinopa
items.content_text: Male and female of this species have different markings

items.title: Discophlebia lucasii
items.content_text: Second image shows side view. Worn specimen with damaged wing tips.

items.title: Nola delograpta
items.content_text: Small, white moth with very dark markings, typical Nola antennae.

items.title: Scoparia plagiotis
items.content_text: Small crambid moth - pale brown with darker brown patches on forewing.

items.title: Calamidia hirta
items.content_text: Plain brown, narrow-winged moth with wingspan approaching 40 mm. Plain yellow hindwings.

items.title: Gallaba eugraphes
items.content_text: Medium sized, distinctive moth. The female is similar but bipectinate antennae are not as broad as with the males.

items.title: Munychryia senicula
items.content_text: Attractive grey moth with dark transverse lines.

items.title: Asura lydia
items.content_text: Small yellow moth with dark lines

items.title: Tineodes adactylalis
items.content_text: Small moth; Narrow forewings folded longitudinally giving a distorted appearance.

items.title: Atheropla decaspila
items.content_text: Small, cream coloured moth with dark rounded spots along the termen; dark speckled transverse baron outer fifth; five small but obvious spots on forewing. Upturned palpi curved back over head.

items.title: Heteroteucha parvula
items.content_text: Adult moth; Forewing yellow on inner two thirds with outer third suffused with orange; dark transverse line at two thirds extending from trailing edge to middle.

items.title: Cryptoblabes spp.
items.content_text: Two images - dorsal and side view.

items.title: Epitymbia cosmota
items.content_text: Note the different appearance of the female compared to the male.

items.title: Epitymbia cosmota
items.content_text: Male and female of this species are visually quite different.

items.title: Schrankia costaestrigalis
items.content_text: Two side views included in extra images

items.title: Pararguda nasuta
items.content_text: Second image shows side view and underside of hindwing.
